

{input} using curly brakets creates a splain group. The inner inputs are then used to generate and raplace

{'input1' "input2"} '' and  "" dictate literals that shouldn't be compiled allowing you to use static

{'input'?n} only compile the preceding input with a chance of 1 in n

{input1|input2} input one or input 2

processing order
Splain will first do any conditionals (|)and then (?)
Then it will compile tokens


splain templates:

weather: {
    really-cold:[
    "freezing",
    "icy",
    "sub-zero"
    ]
    cold:{
    "{{weather.really-cold}}",
    "nippy"
    }
}